{"id":"agagite","term":"Agagite","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A name applied to Haman and also to his father (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Esther 3:1\">Esther 3:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:10\">10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:3\">8:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:5\">5</a>). Probably it was equivalent to Amalekite.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Esther 3:1","Genesis 1:10","Genesis 8:3","Genesis 8:5"]}